nib.text:
One person died in an apartment fire Wednesday morning in Hamline-Midway, officials said.

At approximately 9:45 a.m., firefighters responded to reports of a residential fire in the 1700 block of Englewood Avenue.

Firefighters arrived on the scene and quickly contained the fire to one apartment unit.
While searching the apartment complex, firefighters found an injured victim.

The victim was transported to an area hospital where they were pronounced deceased.

According to [KARE](https://www.kare11.com/article/news/local/one-killed-in-apartment-fire/89-26d0d46d-7bf1-44d5-8c8f-927681b58bb0?utm_campaign=snd-autopilot), SPFD officials said the cause of the fire does not appear to be suspicious.

An investigation is ongoing.
